      <div class="poemandimg">
       <div class="poem">
        In Naruto, the series opens with the introduction of Naruto Uzumaki, a spirited orphan with a grand ambition: to become the Hokage, the revered leader of his village. Despite the villagers' disdain for him as the host of the Nine-Tailed Fox spirit, Naruto remains resolute. Alongside classmates Sakura Haruno and Sasuke Uchiha, under the tutelage of their sensei Kakashi Hatake, Naruto navigates the challenges of the Ninja Academy. Their journey is fraught with peril, including encounters with notorious figures like Orochimaru, a rogue ninja obsessed with power and immortality. Additionally, Sasuke harbors a personal vendetta against his brother, Itachi Uchiha, further complicating their dynamics. The Chunin Exams emerge as a defining moment, testing not only their skills but also their bonds of friendship against rival ninja from other villages. Naruto's early narrative lays a sturdy groundwork for the series, weaving themes of perseverance and friendship amidst the trials and tribulations of the ninja world.</div>
